film and discussion mammy water in search of the water spirits in nigeria film and discussion mammy water in search of the water spirits in nigeria facebook twitter email print add to calendar this documentary film by director sabine jell bahlsen takes an in depth look at the worship of mammy water and the people ceremonies and places affected by this goddess of the water 1989 59 minutes presented in conjunction with the exhibition mami wata arts for water spirits in africa and its diasporas the first major american exhibition to present a comprehensive examination of the dynamic visual arts associated with water spirits when thursday november 18 2010 6 00 pm approximate duration of 2 hour s where cantor arts center just off palm drive at museum way and lomita drive map audience faculty staff alumni friends general public students members tags film international arts contact 723 4177 admission free permalink http events stanford edu events 245 24529 more info last modified november 12 2010
